[size=4][u]Unassigned Plus[/u][/size]

Adds an [b]Unassigned Plus[/b] tab to the [b]Property Owned[/b] menu in the map, placed next to the vanilla Unassigned Ships tab. A dropdown at the top of the tab lets you auto-group unassigned ships into folders by Type, Size, Order, Sector, or any combination of all four - with optional collapsible groups and hierarchical nesting.

[size=3][u][b]Features[/b][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] [b]Unassigned Plus tab[/b]: A dedicated tab in the Property Owned menu lists all unassigned ships with the same ship rows as the vanilla view - hull bars, action buttons, and sub-expansion all work exactly as in the vanilla tab.
[*] [b]Flexible grouping[/b]: Ships can be grouped by any single dimension or any combination of up to four dimensions: [b]Type[/b] (Purpose), [b]Size[/b], [b]Order[/b], [b]Sector[/b]. All permutations are available in the dropdown.
[*] [b]Hierarchical groups[/b]: When multiple grouping dimensions are selected, enable the [b]Hierarchical[/b] checkbox to render groups as a nested tree of headers rather than flat concatenated labels.
[*] [b]Collapsible groups[/b]: Enable the [b]Collapsible[/b] checkbox to add +/- toggle buttons to group headers. A master expand/collapse button appears in the section header row. Collapsed state is preserved when re-opening the tab.
[*] [b]Group ordering[/b]: Purpose groups follow a logical role order (Fight, Auxiliary, Trade, Mine, Salvage, Build, Other); Size groups are sorted largest-first; Order and Sector groups are sorted alphabetically.
[*] [b]Save configuration[/b]: When the [b]Save Tab configuration on change[/b] option is enabled (default: on), the current grouping mode, hierarchical, and collapsible settings are persisted to the save file and restored on the next session.
[*] [b]Hide vanilla tab[/b]: Optionally hide the original Unassigned Ships tab to reduce clutter.
[*] [b]Tab positioning[/b]: The tab is placed immediately after the vanilla Unassigned Ships tab.
[*] [b]Compatible with X4 8.00 and 9.00[/b].
[/list]
